<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <title><%= pageTitle %> - AttendanceMS</title>
  <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
  <link href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.4.0/css/all.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
  <style>
    :root { --primary-gradient: linear-gradient(135deg, #667eea 0%, #764ba2 100%); }
    body { background-color: #f8f9fa; font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; }
    .help-header { background: var(--primary-gradient); color: white; padding: 3rem 0 2rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
    .guide-card { background: white; border-radius: 15px; padding: 2rem; box-shadow: 0 5px 15px rgba(0,0,0,0.1); margin-bottom: 2rem; }
    .step-number { background: var(--primary-gradient); color: white; width: 30px; height: 30px; border-radius: 50%; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-weight: 700; margin-right: 1rem; }
    .back-nav { position: fixed; top: 2rem; right: 2rem; z-index: 1000; }
    @media (max-width: 768px) { .back-nav { position: relative; top: auto; right: auto; margin-bottom: 1rem; } }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="back-nav">
    <a href="/help" class="btn btn-outline-primary me-2"><i class="fas fa-arrow-left me-2"></i>Back to Help</a>
    <a href="/dashboard" class="btn btn-primary"><i class="fas fa-tachometer-alt me-2"></i>Dashboard</a>
  </div>

  <div class="help-header">
    <div class="container">
      <h1><i class="fas fa-tasks me-3"></i>How-To Guides</h1>
      <p class="lead">Step-by-step instructions for common tasks in AttendanceMS</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="container">
    <div class="guide-card" id="add-class">
      <h3><i class="fas fa-plus-circle me-2"></i>How to Add a New Class</h3>
      <div class="d-flex align-items-start mb-3">
        <div class="step-number">1</div>
        <div><strong>Navigate to Classes:</strong> From your dashboard, click "Manage Classes" or "Create Class"</div>
      </div>
      <div class="d-flex align-items-start mb-3">
        <div class="step-number">2</div>
        <div><strong>Fill Details:</strong> Enter class name, section, academic year, and description</div>
      </div>
      <div class="d-flex align-items-start mb-3">
        <div class="step-number">3</div>
        <div><strong>Save Class:</strong> Click "Create Class" to save your new class</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="guide-card" id="import-students">
      <h3><i class="fas fa-upload me-2"></i>How to Import Students from CSV</h3>
      <div class="d-flex align-items-start mb-3">
        <div class="step-number">1</div>
        <div><strong>Prepare CSV:</strong> Create a CSV file with columns: name, roll_no, parent_email, parent_phone</div>
      </div>
      <div class="d-flex align-items-start mb-3">
        <div class="step-number">2</div>
        <div><strong>Go to Import:</strong> In your class, click "Import Students" button</div>
      </div>
      <div class="d-flex align-items-start mb-3">
        <div class="step-number">3</div>
        <div><strong>Upload File:</strong> Select your CSV file and click "Import"</div>
      </div>
      <div class="d-flex align-items-start mb-3">
        <div class="step-number">4</div>
        <div><strong>Review & Confirm:</strong> Check the preview and confirm the import</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="guide-card" id="mark-attendance">
      <h3><i class="fas fa-check me-2"></i>How to Mark Attendance</h3>
      <div class="d-flex align-items-start mb-3">
        <div class="step-number">1</div>
        <div><strong>Open Attendance:</strong> Click "Daily Attendance" from dashboard</div>
      </div>
      <div class="d-flex align-items-start mb-3">
        <div class="step-number">2</div>
        <div><strong>Select Class & Date:</strong> Choose your class and the date</div>
      </div>
      <div class="d-flex align-items-start mb-3">
        <div class="step-number">3</div>
        <div><strong>Mark Students:</strong> Click on each student to mark Present/Absent/Late/Excused</div>
      </div>
      <div class="d-flex align-items-start mb-3">
        <div class="step-number">4</div>
        <div><strong>Save:</strong> Click "Save Attendance" to record the data</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="guide-card" id="generate-reports">
      <h3><i class="fas fa-chart-bar me-2"></i>How to Generate Reports</h3>
      <div class="d-flex align-items-start mb-3">
        <div class="step-number">1</div>
        <div><strong>Go to Reports:</strong> Click "Reports" from the main menu</div>
      </div>
      <div class="d-flex align-items-start mb-3">
        <div class="step-number">2</div>
        <div><strong>Select Type:</strong> Choose Daily, Weekly, or Monthly report</div>
      </div>
      <div class="d-flex align-items-start mb-3">
        <div class="step-number">3</div>
        <div><strong>Set Parameters:</strong> Select class, date range, and format</div>
      </div>
      <div class="d-flex align-items-start mb-3">
        <div class="step-number">4</div>
        <div><strong>Generate:</strong> Click "Generate Report" to create and download</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>